The '''Flag of Kiev''' is a rectangular piece of fabric that is azure in colour. The coat of arms of Kiev is placed in the centre of the flag, which represents the [[Michael (archangel)|Archangel Michael]] in white robes, holding a flaming sword in his right hand and a shield in his left hand.

The flag and coat of arms were adopted by a resolution of the City Council of Kiev in 1995.

