The '''history of rail transport in the Comoros''' began in about 1907.  The only railway to be built in the Comoros was a {{RailGauge|600mm|lk=on}} [[Narrow gauge railway|narrow gauge]] [[industrial railway]].  Its owner was a plantation society, the ''Société Comores Bambaoa''.  The railway carried only freight traffic. It is not known when the railway was abandoned.

