The '''Makere ''' are an ethnic group of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], living near the [[Bima River]] in the Northern part of the country.<ref name="HealeYong2009">{{cite book|last1=Heale|first1=Jay |last2=Yong|first2=Jui Lin|title=Democratic Republic of the Congo|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9nxFwxF7nCsC&pg=PA74|year=2009|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-4478-7|page=74}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|first=Amina Blackwood|last= Meeks|chapter=Depths of Memories: Honouring the Makere People|editors=Carmen Birkle, Nicole Waller|title="The Sea is History": Exploring the Atlantic|date=2009|publisher=Winter|location=Heidelberg|isbn=9783825356125|pages=57-}}</ref> They speak the [[Mangbetu language]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Congo Expedition: Regions, Languages and Tribes. Excerpted from: ''African Reflections: Art from Northeastern Zaire'', Schildkrout and Keim, Chapter 1, AMNH and University of Washington Press, 1990.|url=http://diglib1.amnh.org/articles/anthro/excerpt4.html|website=diglib1.amnh.org|accessdate=11 March 2018}}</ref>

