{{unreferenced|date=October 2007}}

'''Makwayera''' is an African style of choral singing that native [[Zimbabwe]]ans developed by combining elements of their traditional vocal music with the western four-part harmony brought to the region by [[missionaries]]. It includes elements of call and response and a strong vocal leader.  The most famous singer of this style of music is the LPP.

