{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Getafe |latin = Dioecesis Xetafensis |local = Diócesis de Getafe |image = Escudo de la Diócesis de Getafe.svg |caption = Coat of arms of Getafe |country = {{flag|Spain}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Madrid|Madrid]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Madrid|Madrid]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = [[Getafe Cathedral|Cathedral of St. Mary Magdalene in Getafe]] |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 2,295 |population = 1,365,668 |population_as_of = 2006 |catholics = 1,229,101 |catholics_percent= 90.0 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Joaquín María López de Andújar y Cánovas del Castillo]] |metro_archbishop = [[Carlos Osoro]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= [[José Rico Pavés]] |map = Diócesis de Getafe.svg |website = [http://www.diocesisgetafe.es/ Website of the Diocese] }}
The '''Diocese of Getafe ''' ({{lang-la|Xetafen(sis)}}) is a Roman Catholic ecclesiastical territory in Spain, part of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Madrid|Archdiocese of Madrid]]. The seat is in the city of [[Getafe]], in the [[Getafe Cathedral]]. [[File:Getafe - Catedral de Nuestra Señora de la Magdalena 02.jpg|thumb|Getafe Cathedral]] It was established on July 23, 1991, from the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Madrid]]. The current Bishop is [[Joaquín María López de Andújar y Cánovas del Castillo]].
